Rakuen's Kel'Shadra witnessing office during the Violet Compact era extended Midgaard's Sealed Names apparatus to the southern frontier.
Persons resettled south could register testimonies through the office — appearing to be testimony preservation but functioning as suppression, routing claims to classification levels beyond practical access: "below bell-line; no civic remainder."
In Khenari descent accounting, these are testimonies that exist in the system but cannot be reached — present without accessible location, documented without recoverable substance.
The office closed at the end of the Violet Compact era without explanation. Its records are in the Kel'Shadra crypt apparatus, some concerning Rakuen arrivals with inconvenient things to say about who ordered their resettlement.
The Bloom Council accepted the witnessing office arrangement without fully investigating its classification procedures — ignorance or deliberate non-inquiry; both produce the same outcome.
