Rakuen's position is structurally determined: Midgaard controls the southern gate and registry; Woodland cells control interior approaches; Rakuen absorbs whatever arrives downstream with no power to compel upstream actors.
This logistical trap was identified by Caitha Dunnmark in Year 34 and has not changed.
The Quiet Separatist maritime track through Mafdet is the only proposed route not depending on Midgaard's cooperation.
Its viability depends on: commercial significance of Rakuen's canopy-botanical trade, management of Red Sand Accounts debt-leverage risk, whether Reach Wardens and Sand-Sea Carters' Guild would block access, and whether mercy-freight classification extends to non-disaster commercial routes.
The Garden Ledger Clerks' triangular evidence structure connecting Midgaard, Kowloon, and Rakuen through the Conclave guilt chain is also a network connection.
The same three nodes forming the trade subsidy dependency form the three documented points of the Conclave transfer chain.
